+### 2026-03-09 - Phase 2 Plan Execution Batches (`full-enhance`, run `20260309-205940-full-enhance`)
+
+#### Selected Batch
+- Batch A remains the highest-value bounded implementation pass:
+  - `SUP-ROUTE-001`
+  - `SUP-UX-001`
+  - `SUP-API-001`
+- Why this batch fits now:
+  - it resolves three linked high-priority gaps in one protected account surface (`sidebar.jsx`, `AppRoutes.jsx`, `OperatorResponse`, and the scoped support API clients)
+  - the backend v1 complaint/request/review/objection endpoints already exist and already have focused backend coverage, so the missing work is frontend consumer wiring rather than new contract design
+  - it produces the largest visible improvement without reopening the separate chat contract or backend test-environment work in the same implementation phase
+
+#### Planning Corrections and Constraints
+- The current `OperatorResponse` review CTA must not be keyed only from the frontend "approved" presentation. The live backend review endpoint accepts submissions only when `booking_status` is `Completed`, `Closed`, or `Close`.
+- The safest navigation decision for the same batch is:
+  - keep `Help & Complaints` only if a real protected `/help` route is added and backed by `supportApi.js`
+  - remove the dead `/reviews` sidebar link unless a real route owner is introduced in the same batch, and instead make review submission a contextual action from the booking follow-up surface
+- `/messages` should stay outside Batch A. The existing backend chat contract is `/chat/*`, uses `IsAdminUser` permissions, and still relies on session tokens in the URL path, so it is not a drop-in authenticated web-panel replacement.
+
+#### Deferred Batches
+- Batch B: `MSG-001`
+  - preferred direction is hide/remove until a user-safe chat contract exists or a deliberate API migration is scoped
+- Batch C: `BE-ENV-001` + `BE-TEST-001`
+  - add a test-specific DB override first, rerun the focused suite, then normalize `booking_status_time_idx` only if it still fails on a fresh local test database
+
+#### Verification Plan
+- Batch A verification should stay frontend-scoped:
+  - authenticated route tracing for `/help`, `/operator-response`, and the updated sidebar state
+  - consumer tracing confirming `supportApi.js` owns the live support flow and the legacy helpers are removable
+  - scoped frontend static checks and `npm run build` for `Huz-Web-Frontend`
+- Backend `python manage.py check` and the focused Django tests remain deferred to Batch C because the current remote-DB dependency still blocks non-interactive reproducibility.
+- No target-project code changed in this phase.
